The paper deals with developing a framework to assist non-specialists in formulating database queries. This involves developing algorithms to infer queries from a set of examples and their explanations. The paper also discusses the implementation of a system prototype with an interface that assists users in formulating explanations in an intuitive way. Given these aspects, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms to infer queries, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses the use of models of data provenance, which makes cs.LG (Learning) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves a user study and an interface design, which makes cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a likely sub-category as well.
